&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is 93.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;According to the scheme recommended by the Cabinet Mission. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The arrangement was: &lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;292 members were elected through the Provincial Legislative Assemblies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;93 members represented the Indian Princely States;&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;4 members represented the Chief Commissioners&amp;#39; Provinces.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, option 2&amp;nbsp;is the correct answer.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As to its composition, members were &lt;strong&gt;chosen by indirect election&lt;/strong&gt; by the members of the Provincial Legislative Assemblies.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;On 9th&amp;nbsp;December 1946, the Constituent Assembly of India met for the first time in the Constitution Hall now popularly referred to as Central Hall of Parliament House.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;207 members were present who signed the register and submitted their credentials. As of December 1947, the Assembly had 299 members: 229 members elected from 12 Indian Provinces and&lt;strong&gt; 70 members nominated from 29 Princely States.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Constitution of India was adopted on 26 November 1949 and the hon&amp;#39;ble members appended their signatures to it on 24 January 1950.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In all, 284 members actually signed the Constitution. On that day when the Constitution was being signed, it was drizzling outside and it was interpreted as a sign of a good omen.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Constitution of India came into force on 2 6 January 1950.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;On that day, the Assembly ceased to exist, transforming itself into the Provisional Parliament of India until a new Parliament was constituted in 1952.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is 15.&lt;/p&gt;

