&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The constitution of India was drafted by a body named the Constituent Assembly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Its members were indirectly elected according to a plan put forth by the British Cabinet Mission of 1946.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The assembly included members selected by the provincial legislatures of British India as well as representatives chosen by the rulers of the princely states.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rajendra Prasad&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

